-- synthesis of the doubly-sliced opens `HasSheafify`/`WEqualsLocallyBijective` instances
-- `((J.over X).over Y)вҖҰ`, whose default-heartbeat search times out (it succeeds when bumped).
/-- **Reduction of quasi-coherence of an iso-pushforward to the per-slice case** (Need #1 `hqc`,
`of_coversTop` wiring). Given a quasi-coherence datum `q` for `H` and quasi-coherence of the
restricted pushforward `(ПҶ_* H).over (ПҶ.inv вҒ»В№бөҒ (q.X i))` over each preimage cover member, the
pushforward `ПҶ_* H` is quasi-coherent.  Project-local: wires Mathlib's
`IsQuasicoherent.of_coversTop` to the cover-transport `coversTop_preimage_of_iso`, isolating the
residual per-slice obligation. -/
lemma pushforward_iso_qcoh_of_slice_qcoh {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (ПҶ : X вү… Y) (H : X.Modules)
    (q : SheafOfModules.QuasicoherentData.{u, u, u, u} H)
    (hslice : вҲҖ i, (((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ПҶ).functor.obj H).over
        (ПҶ.inv вҒ»В№бөҒ q.X i)).IsQuasicoherent) :
    ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ПҶ).functor.obj H).IsQuasicoherent := by
  haveI : вҲҖ i, (((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ПҶ).functor.obj H).over
      (ПҶ.inv вҒ»В№бөҒ q.X i)).IsQuasicoherent := hslice
  exact SheafOfModules.IsQuasicoherent.of_coversTop
    ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ПҶ).functor.obj H) (fun i => ПҶ.inv вҒ»В№бөҒ q.X i)
    (coversTop_preimage_of_iso ПҶ q.X q.coversTop)

/-! ## Project-local Mathlib supplement вҖ” the slice structure-sheaf ring map `ПҲ_r` (Need #1 `hqc`)

The genuine wall of `hqc`: a single cross-ring slice structure-sheaf ring map `ПҲ_r` from which the
colimit-preserving `SheafOfModules.pullback ПҲ_r` is built.  For a scheme iso `ПҶ : X вү… Y` and an open
`Uбөў вҠҶ X` with image `Vбөў = ПҶ.invвҒ»В№бөҒ Uбөў вҠҶ Y`, the underlying opens-equivalence functor is
`FвӮҖ = Opens.map ПҶ.inv.base : Opens X вҘӨ Opens Y` (sending `Uбөў` to `Vбөў` by `rfl`).  Its slice version
`Over.post FвӮҖ : Over Uбөў вҘӨ Over Vбөў` is continuous and final (both because `FвӮҖ` is an equivalence,
`ПҶ` being an iso).  The map `ПҲ_r` is the slice of the structure-sheaf comparison
`ПҶ.inv.toRingCatSheafHom : рқ’Ә_X вҹ¶ (FвӮҖ.sheafPushforwardContinuous _ _ _).obj рқ’Ә_Y`, obtained simply by
applying the over-pullback functor `(Opens.grothendieckTopology X).overPullback RingCat Uбөў`; the
codomain matches the desired sliced pushforward by the BeckвҖ“Chevalley identity
`Over.post FвӮҖ вӢҷ Over.forget Vбөў = Over.forget Uбөў вӢҷ FвӮҖ` (`rfl`). -/

section SlicePsi

open TopologicalSpace

variable {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (ПҶ : X вү… Y) (Ui : X.Opens)

/-- `Opens.map ПҶ.inv.base` is an equivalence (its base is the homeomorphism underlying `ПҶ`).
Project-local instance feeding the continuity and finality of the slice functor `Over.post`. -/
instance opensMapInvBase_isEquivalence : (Opens.map ПҶ.inv.base).IsEquivalence :=
  inferInstanceAs (Opens.mapMapIso (Scheme.forgetToTop.mapIso ПҶ).symm).functor.IsEquivalence

/-- The slice functor `Over.post (Opens.map ПҶ.inv.base) : Over Uбөў вҘӨ Over Vбөў` is continuous for the
over-Grothendieck-topologies.  Project-local: from `coverPreserving_opens_map` lifted to the slices
via `CoverPreserving.overPost`, plus `compatiblePreservingOfFlat` (the slice functor is flat, being
an equivalence). -/
instance overPost_slice_isContinuous :
    (Over.post (X := Ui) (Opens.map ПҶ.inv.base)).IsContinuous
      ((Opens.grothendieckTopology X).over Ui)
      ((Opens.grothendieckTopology Y).over (ПҶ.inv вҒ»В№бөҒ Ui)) :=
  Functor.isContinuous_of_coverPreserving
    (compatiblePreservingOfFlat _ _)
    (CoverPreserving.overPost Ui (coverPreserving_opens_map ПҶ.inv.base))

